The paper proposes a deep learning solution for stock prediction, which involves modeling sequential data and capturing the relations between stocks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves modeling temporal data and graph structures, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves data analysis and experimentation, which could fall under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
